  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Grand Aigle is a very stylish four-star hotel renovated in a local, traditional chalet style.. The interior is modern combining warm woods and cool stone to create an inviting atmosphere of cosiness. Offered on a half board basis, you can enjoy delicious meals from the comfortable restaurant. The hotel benefits from all of the facilities you would need for the perfect holiday. Access to the ski area is easy, with the ability to ski-in/ski-out of the hotel. There are also many opportunities to relax - take a seat in front of the open fire in the evening or enjoy the benefits of the Pure Altitude spa located in the hotel cellar.</p>
<h2>Spa facilities </h2>
<p>Treat yourself to a rest day and choose from one of the many beneficial therapies available at the Grand Aigle's Spa. Pure Altitude never fails to deliver the benefits of fresh mountain air and many of the treatments on offer are infused with edelweiss - a symbolic plant of the Alps. Enjoy the warmth of a jacuzzi or sauna after a day in the snow and allow yourself to sink into relaxation with a full body massage. Access to the spa is around <span>€15 per person for 45 minutes.  </span></p>
<h2>Ideal location</h2>
<p>Located in the heart of <a data-udi="umb://document/b7e31f4645514434bec76a3728e974c0" href="/{localLink:umb://document/b7e31f4645514434bec76a3728e974c0}" title="Serre Chevalier">Serre Chevalier</a>, the Grand Aigle Hotel offers picturesque views of the resort, and convenient access to the slopes. Exit the boot room and walk (or ski if weather permitting) 450 metres downhill to the Pontillas gondola for access to over 250 kilometres of high quality, varied terrain. The hotel is found in the Guisane Valley near the Italian border and benefits from 300 days of sunshine - so keep a camera on hand and be prepared for many perfect photo moments. </p>
<h2>Food and drink</h2>
<p>The attractive restaurant <span>L'Aiglon </span>offers a continental breakfast buffet of healthy sweet and savoury items, so you can fuel up for a day on the slopes. Each day you can enjoy a three course meal and even sample alpine specialities such as fondue or raclette (pay locally). Stop by the bar before heading to bed to really make the most of the evening experience. with a selection of cocktails, hot drinks and tapas available, we're sure you'll find something to fill your appetite.</p>]]></description>
