  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Classic Double Rooms</strong> are around 15m² and sleep two people with a double bed. Please note that the bed cannot be separated. </p>
<p><strong>Superior Double Rooms </strong>are around 19m² sleeping two people. These rooms can either be made up as two single beds or one double bed - please confirm your preference at the time of booking. Please note that these rooms do not have lift access.</p>
<p><strong>Deluxe Double Rooms</strong><strong> </strong>are around 21m² sleeping two people.  These rooms can either be made up as two single beds or one double bed - please confirm your preference at the time of booking.</p>
<p><strong>Triple Rooms</strong> are around 23m² and sleep two to three people and with a double bed or twin beds, and can facilitate an additional single bed. These rooms are on request, please give our Reservations team a call to book.</p>
<p><strong>Quad Rooms </strong>are around 23m² and sleep four people.  These rooms are on request, please give our Reservations team a call to book.</p>
<p><span>Please note that Deluxe rooms are situated in an adjacent older building, connected via an indoor corridor and do not have lift access. </span></p>
<p><strong>Room facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Satellite TV</li>
<li>Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Telephone</li>
<li>Nespresso coffee machine </li>
<li>Mini bar</li>
<li>Toiletries</li>
<li>Bed Linen</li>
<li>Towels</li>
<li>Hair dryer</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Bath with showerhead attachment</li>
<li>Bath robes and slippers (on request)</li>
<li>Ironing facilities (on request)</li>
<li>Wake up service (on request)</li>
<li>Beds are made on arrival and house keeping is included.</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>]]></roomsDescription>
